20next%20level%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20that%20simply%20asking%20those%20two%20questions%20gives%20you%20tremendous%20clarity%20on%20the%20path%20to%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20easy%20to%20assume%20that%20you%20should%20only%20take%20on%20more%20responsibilities%20after%20getting%20promoted%2C%20but%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20things%20I've%20learned%20about%20promotions%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20at%20large%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20is%20that%20you%20get%20promoted%20when%20you're%20already%20operating%20at%20the%20next%20seniority%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20dos%20and%20don'ts%20if%20you'd%20like%20to%20try%20it%20for%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bfca74d-f03f-408e-8b94-79392617929b%5C%22%3EDo%20speak%20with%20your%20manager%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20kept%20a%20specific%20document%20outlining%20what%20was%20expected%20at%20each%20level.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20%26quot%3Bidentifying%20obstacles%20or%20risks%20to%20a%20project%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20Level%203%20responsibility%2C%20Level%204%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Bidentifying%20obstacles%20or%20risks%20to%20a%20project%20and%20proactively%20putting%20a%20mitigation%20plan%20in%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20assume%20you're%20doing%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20or%20that%20you're%20already%20operating%20at%20a%20more%20senior%20level%20when%20you%20don't%20know%20exactly%20what%20that%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20these%20conversations%2C%20I%20had%20clarity%20and%20knew%20precisely%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20do%20to%20meet%20and%20exceed%20expectations%20so%20I'd%20have%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-promotion-pay-raise-career-growth-questions-for-manager-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest%20chance%20for%20a%20promotion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20next%20cycle%3B%20it%20was%20as%20if%20I%20had%20a%20blueprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'd%20mastered%20the%20role%20of%20an%20associate%2C%20it%20was%20time%20to%20start%20taking%20on%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20a%20senior%20associate%2C%20delivering%20Level%204%20quality%20work%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20my%20manager%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-moved-desk-in-office-promotion-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehad%20visibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ace960c1-4b2c-4631-b815-0d90a3fa6778%5C%22%3EDo%20take%20action%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20an%20associate%20on%20the%20sales%20productivity%20team%20at%20LinkedIn%2C%20our%20goal%20was%20to%20find%20innovative%20ways%20to%20increase%20sales%20quota%20attainment.%20In%20my%20junior%20role%2C%20I%20executed%20smaller%20aspects%20of%20that%20goal%2C%20such%20as%20creating%20reports%20and%20slide%20decks%20that%20summarized%20our%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20then%20reviewed%20those%20presentations%20every%20quarter%20with%2020%20global%20stakeholders%20on%20the%20sales%20leadership%20team.%20These%20stakeholder%20meetings%20were%20time-consuming%20for%20my%20manager%2C%20but%20necessary%20to%20ensure%20everyone%20was%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20offered%20to%20not%20only%20create%20the%20slide%20decks%2C%20but%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresentation-tips-powerpoint-public-speaking-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epresenting%20them%20myself%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20it%20was%20uncommon%20for%20an%20associate%20to%20manage%20a%20meeting%20with%20senior%20vice%20presidents%2C%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20something%20a%20senior%20associate%20would%20try%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20was%20open%20to%20it%2C%20and%20he%20let%20me%20present%20at%20one%20of%20the%20meetings.%20After%20that%20presentation%2C%20he%20allowed%20me%20to%20take%20over%20more%20and%20more%20stakeholder%20updates.%20After%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20I%20was%20fully%20owning%20all%20stakeholder%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20manager%20had%20more%20time%20to%20work%20on%20our%20team's%20strategy%2C%20and%20I%20got%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgot-pay-raise-lazy-girl-strategy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eweekly%20visibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20senior%20executives.%20The%20executives%20were%20often%20shocked%20when%20they%20found%20out%20I%20was%20only%20an%20associate%2C%20since%20I%20was%20doing%20the%20role%20of%20a%20senior%20associate%20or%20even%20manager.%20Their%20votes%20of%20confidence%20helped%20tremendously%20in%20the%20next%20promotion%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pitch-change-in-role-to-your-manager-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epromotion%20discussions%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20around%2C%20my%20manager%20could%20easily%20advocate%20for%20me%20because%20I%20was%20already%20operating%20at%20that%20higher%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c28062ee-110f-4d8b-8f53-b961db0922a8%5C%22%3EDo%20make%20sure%20it's%20for%20a%20role%20you%20truly%20want%20and%20avoid%20burnout%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20will%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareerist-corporate-ladder-decline-promotions-work-ethic-american-dream-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclimbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%3C%2Fa%3E%20simply%20because%20there%20are%20more%20ladder%20rungs%20in%20front%20of%20them.%20Then%2C%20when%20they%20get%20to%20the%20top%2C%20they%20realize%20this%20isn't%20what%20they%20wanted%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20another%20reason%20it's%20important%20to%20get%20clarity%20on%20what's%20expected%20at%20each%20level.%20By%20doing%20so%2C%20you%20get%20a%20little%20glimpse%20into%20what%20your%20future%20work%20life%20could%20be%20if%20you%20continue%20on%20that%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20start%20picking%20up%20extra%20tasks%2C%20make%20sure%20you're%20doing%20it%20for